text: Sonora is an extinct town in Atchison County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. The GNIS classifies it as a populated place. Sonora was laid out in 1846. A post office called Sonora was established in 1872, and closed in 1875. ==References== Category:Ghost towns in Missouri Category:Former populated places in Atchison County, Missouri
title: Sonora, Missouri
